      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 49: Using originalPriority to decide whether to start foreground-service call handling can treat an FCM message that was delivered as normal priority as high priority. On Android versions with background foreground-service restrictions, a downgraded message may no longer have the high-priority FCM exemption, so this can still fail or create inconsistent behavior despite the exception handler. Keep originalPriority for the daemon connectivity wake-up if that is the intended signal, but use delivered priority for foreground-service eligibility, for example:\\n```suggestion\\n        val isCallPush \u003d pushType.contains(\\\"audioCall\\\") || pushType.contains(\\\"videoCall\\\")\\n        val canStartCallForegroundService \u003d isCallPush \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\\n        val shouldReconnectForCall \u003d isCallPush \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\\n```",
